## SSH

From founder laptop: `ssh root@<ip>` — uses default `~/.ssh/` key (no `-i` flag).

For CI/CD: GitHub Actions secrets `HETZNER_HOST`, `HETZNER_SSH_KEY`, `HETZNER_HOST_FINGERPRINT` (currently point to paperwork-ops; update for new boxes as needed).

## Secrets per box

| Box | Env file path | Populated from |
|---|---|---|
| paperwork-ops | `/opt/paperwork-ops/.env` | Studio Vault (existing) |
| paperwork-builders | `/opt/paperwork-build/.env` | Studio Vault via `make secrets` |
| paperwork-workers | `/opt/paperwork-workers/.env` | Studio Vault via `make secrets` |

## Hetzner API token

If programmatic management needed (rescale, snapshot, list servers): look up `HETZNER_API_TOKEN` in Studio Vault. If missing, generate at console.hetzner.cloud > Security > API Tokens, store in vault.

## Scaling triggers (do NOT buy another box until one of these is true)

1. Sustained >70% CPU on paperwork-builders for 7 consecutive days
2. Sustained >70% RAM on paperwork-workers for 7 consecutive days
3. AxiomFolio walk-forward batches move to Hetzner (WS-83)
4. Brain B2C launch needs separate background box
5. CX53 stock returns in Helsinki — in-place rescale paperwork-workers CX43 → CX53 (brief reboot, same IP)

## Don't

- Never paste secrets into compose files (read from .env)
- Never put SSH private keys in repo (always vault or GH secrets)
- Never enable password auth on these boxes (key-only)
- Never run production workloads on paperwork-ops (it's state + social only)
